{
  "texts": [
    "For consumers, lack of confidence in a new technology will cause reluctance to adopt, and this finding is vital in any financial transaction (Howcroft et al., 2002).",
    "In another study, Kim et al. (2022) added the factor of trust to TAM in examining online banking information systems adoption and results showed significant positive effect of trust on perceived usefulness and behavioral intention.",
    "Trust has been reported as a crucial factor in understanding the behaviour of technology adoption (Van Pinxteren et al., 2019).",
    "Chi et al. (2021) developed the Social Service Robot Interaction Trust (SSRIT) framework that demonstrates trust in interactions with AI robots as a notion that the interaction that customer has with AI social robots can produce favorable outcomes of service.",
    "From the outcomes, the authors concluded that the trust that customers have towards human-robot interaction entails a higher-order construct resulting from the assessment of different factors."
  ]
}